ress\n\nFor MySQL (mainline/achievement):\n- GetQuestProgress(ctx, uid, questID 
string) (*QuestProgress, error)\n- GetQuestProgresses(ctx, uid string) ([]*Quest
Progress, error)\n- SaveQuestProgress(ctx, progress *QuestProgress) error\n- Upd
ateQuestProgress(ctx, uid, questID string, progress int, status int) error\n\nFo
r Redis (daily):\n- GetDailyProgress(ctx, uid, questID, dateKey string) (int64, 
error)\n- IncrDailyProgress(ctx, uid, questID, dateKey string, delta int64) (int
64, error)\n\nWait, actually, I should think about this more carefully. The PRD 
says:\n- Mainline: MySQL, key `quest:{uid}:mainline:{quest_id}`\n- Daily: Redis,
key `quest:{uid}:daily:{quest_id}:20250121`\n- Achievement: MySQL, key `quest:{u
id}:achieve:{quest_id}`\n\nBut we already have the `player_tasks` MySQL table. S
hould I use that for all MySQL-backed quests, or use Redis for everything?\n\nTh
e PRD specifically says:\n- 主线 (Mainline): MySQL\n- 每日 (Daily): Redis\n- 成
就 (Achievement): MySQL\n\nAnd the existing `player_tasks` table has fields: pla
yer_id, task_id, progress, status, etc. This maps perfectly to mainline and achi
evement quests. For daily quests, we use Redis with date suffix.\n\nSo my QuestR
epo interface should handle both:\n- MySQL operations for mainline/achievement\n
- Redis operations for daily\n\nActually, looking at the PRD key examples, they 
seem to be Redis key patterns. But the PRD also explicitly says Mainline and Ach
ievement use MySQL. Let me re-read:\n\n| 类型 | 重置规则 | 存储介质 | 进度 Key 
示例 | 并发规则 |\n|------|----------|----------|---------------|----------|\n| 
主线 (Mainline) | 一次性，永不重置 | MySQL | `quest:{uid}:mainline:{quest_id}` |
所有已解锁任务同时有效 |\n| 每日 (Daily) | 自然日 00:00 重置（懒更新） | Redis |
`quest:{uid}:daily:{quest_id}:20250121` | 所有已解锁任务同时有效 |\n| 成就 (Achi
evement) | 一次性，永不重置 | MySQL | `quest:{uid}:achieve:{quest_id}` | 所有已
解锁任务同时有效 |\n\nYes, the "进度 Key 示例" for MySQL might just be conceptua
l identifiers, not actual Redis keys. The actual storage for MySQL is the `playe
r_tasks` table.\n\nSo the repo interface should be:\n```go\ntype QuestRepo inter
face {\n    // MySQL-backed quest progress (mainline + achievement)\n    GetPlay
erQuest(ctx context.Context, uid int64, questID string) (*PlayerQuest, error)\n 
  GetPlayerQuests(ctx context.Context, uid int64) ([]*PlayerQuest, error)\n    S
avePlayerQuest(ctx context.Context, q *PlayerQuest) error\n    UpdatePlayerQuest
Status(ctx context.Context, uid int64, questID string, progress, status int) err
or\n    \n    // Redis-backed daily quest progress\n    GetDailyProgress(ctx con
text.Context, uid int64, questID string, dateKey string) (int64, error)\n    Inc
rDailyProgress(ctx context.Context, uid int64, questID string, dateKey string, d
elta int64) (int64, error)\n    ClaimDailyReward(ctx context.Context, uid int64,
questID string, dateKey string) (bool, error)\n    IsDailyRewardClaimed(ctx cont
ext.Context, uid int64, questID string, dateKey string) (bool, error)\n}\n```\n\
nWait, for the claim/领奖 logic, the PRD says:\n- 领奖幂等：同一任务的奖励只能领
取一次（每日任务按周期隔离）\n\nFor MySQL quests, the `status` field changes fro
m 2 (claimable) to 3 (claimed) upon claiming.\nFor daily quests, I need to track
whether the reward was claimed for the current date. I can use another Redis key
or a Redis SET/field for this.\n\nLet me use a Redis hash or separate key for da
ily claim status:\n- Progress key: `quest:daily:{uid}:{quest_id}:{date}`\n- Clai
med key: `quest:daily_claimed:{uid}:{date}` as a SET of quest_ids\n\nOr I can st
ore both in a hash:\n- Key: `quest:daily:{uid}:{quest_id}:{date}`\n- Fields: `pr
ogress`, `claimed`\n\nActually, for simplicity and atomicity, let me use:\n- Pro
gress stored as string value at `quest:daily:{uid}:{quest_id}:{dateKey}`\n- Clai
med status stored as member in a SET at `quest:daily_claimed:{uid}:{dateKey}`\n\
